# Portable Agent Paths

Never hardcode absolute paths (e.g. `/Users/alpha/Documents/...`) in agent configuration files. Use `$AGENT_HOME` and relative references instead so the project works for any user on any machine.

## Rules

- `$AGENT_HOME` refers to the agent's home directory (e.g. `agents/corey/`). It is injected as an environment variable at runtime.
- `$AGENT_HOME/workspace` is the agent's working directory.
- For company-wide resources, use paths relative to `$AGENT_HOME/../..` or define a `$COMPANY_ROOT` convention.
- For cross-agent references (e.g. gog-cli docs), use `$AGENT_HOME/../gog-cli.md` not an absolute path.

## Examples

```markdown
❌ BAD — breaks for other users:
- Product context: `/Users/alpha/Documents/community-wolf-paperclip/company/product/context.md`
- See `/Users/alpha/Documents/community-wolf-paperclip/agents/gog-cli.md`

✅ GOOD — portable:
- Product context: `$AGENT_HOME/../../company/product/context.md`
- See `$AGENT_HOME/../gog-cli.md`
```
